  m_Name: Level_09_Cahal Pech
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  levelNumber: 9
  levelName: Cahal Pech
  location: Cayo, Belice
  levelDescription: "Cahal Pech began as one of the oldest known Maya farming settlements
    in western Belize, evolving over nearly two millennia into a royal residence
    and ritual center overlooking the river valley. The site\u2019s 30+ structures\u2014palaces,
    plazas, temples, and hidden passageways\u2014illustrate the steady growth of
    social hierarchy from simple hamlets into organized chiefdoms and early states.
    Fine ceramics, carved bone, and early writing traces show that Cahal Pech was
    once home to a thriving elite lineage deeply connected to the rise of centers
    like Xunantunich and Caracol.\n\nFrom this high ridge, generations of nobles
    watched their world become a civilization."
  requiredStackHeight: 40
